  "title": "F&B Outlet Manager | Salary up to $5000",
  "description": "<p><strong>Salary:</strong> Up to $5,000<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Multiple Locations<br /></p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>The Outlet Manager is responsible for overseeing daily outlet operations, ensuring service quality, and managing staff performance. This role requires strong leadership, attention to detail, and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee and manage daily outlet operations</p></li><li><p>Train, guide, and develop staff to meet operational standards</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with company SOPs and quality control standards</p></li><li><p>Take responsibility for overall outlet performance</p></li><li><p>Plan and coordinate manpower scheduling</p></li><li><p>Manage ordering, stock control, and inventory</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Minimum 1 Year experience in F&B / Management / Management Trainee will be an advantage</li></ul><p><p><p><ul><li>Physically fit</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Able to read Chinese order chits and communicate with Mandarin-speaking customers</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Basic proficiency in English will be an advantage</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Fast learner with the ability to adapt to operational requirements</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Able to work well in a team</li></ul></p></p></p><h3><strong>Personal Attributes</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Pleasant and positive disposition</p></li><li><p>Able to work under pressure</p></li><li><p>Confident and outgoing</p></li><li><p>Observant with strong attention to detail</p></li><li><p>Well-groomed and professional</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Benefits</strong></h3><p><ul><li>Three (3) staff meals provided daily</li><li>Attendance allowance</li><li>Medical claims</li><li>Staff referral incentives</li><li>Career progression opportunities</li></ul><p><strong>Interested candidates are invited to apply.</strong></p></p>",
